        <img class="thumbnail" src="https://static.standard.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2017/05/24/16/shutterstock-501055900.jpg?width=850&fit=bounds&format=pjpg&auto=webp&quality=70">
        <p>What is it? "The new Brighton" — drop that back home to make people feel small and mainstream. Its pier has just been tarted up to the tune of £14 million, and it’s throwing on film festivals and farmers’ markets. In fact — you could basically be in Peckham.</p>
